args: That has to be enough ingredients\nfor the barbecue, right?
Nope. Not yet. The ultimate prey\nhas yet to be caught!
Well, that doesn't sound at all foreboding.
That's right. We gotta go catch us...\na Lord of the Sea!
It's a giant fish species what's been a\nlegend in these parts since ancient times.
We're talkin' a fish so fatty,\nthe meat literally melts in yer mouth!
A master fisherman caught one thirty\nyears ago, but he was the last.
Huh. I had no idea this area\nwas home to such creatures.
Well then, let's go hook a\nroyal addition to our feast.
Are ya kiddin' me? Ya ain't catchin' no\nLord of the Sea with a line and hook!\nIt's way too big for that!
Hell, even if ya DID manage to hook it,\nit'd tear the pole right outta yer hands\nwhile it tears the skin off'a yer palms!
That's...gruesome. So how do we catch it?
We're gonna use this here reinforced net.
They say Lords of the Sea only enter\nthe bay on nights with a full moon.
Hey, there's a full moon tonight!
'Course there is! Why do ya think\nI brought this whole deal up now?
We'll spread this net at the mouth of the\nbay, then wait for dinner to come to us.
Are you sure about this, Ranzal?\nThat net seems awfully empty.
Remember, ain't nobody even seen a\nLord of the Sea in over thirty years.
It ain't gonna just swim up to us\nthe moment we lay a net down.
Hot damn, it's actually in the net!\nLook at the size'a that thing!
I can't believe this actually worked.
Stop doubtin' yer elders already!\nOh, and help me haul this baby in.
Damn, this thing's strong...\nC'mon, you! Quit fightin'!
I think it's too much for us to handle alone!
Maybeâ€”but we ain't givin' up now!
I'm gonna catch me a Lord of the Sea\nand become a legend!
Ranzal, what are you doing?!\nLet go of the net!
That thing's going to drag you out to sea!
I can't let go! I'm caught!
I'd be floatin' face-down right now\nif it wasn't for you.
I'm just glad I got to you in time.
Well, that ain't all I gotta thank ya for.
When ya pulled me up, ya also pulled up\nthe Lord of the Sea I was holdin' onto!
I never imagined it would be so big...
It's nearly twice your size, Ranzal!
Right? I mean, I can eat, but it'd take\nme weeks to plow through that thing.
I guess that means we have everything\nwe need for the barbecue now, right?
Hell, we got MORE than enough.
Time to go get the charcoal lit!
